.TH CINE 1 "2026-07-20" "cine 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cine \- Village Cinemas (Greece) showtimes with IMDB ratings and posters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cine
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Scrapes villagecinemas.gr for what's currently playing, enriches every movie
with its IMDB rating and plot, and shows everything as a poster grid sorted
by rating. Posters render inline via the Kitty graphics protocol (Ghostty,
kitty, WezTerm) with a half-block fallback for other terminals, converted
with
.BR sips (1).
Results are cached for 12 hours. The chosen cinema is remembered between
runs. When output is piped, a plain text list is printed instead of the TUI.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-cinema " " \fIid\fR
Jump straight to a cinema by ID (see \fB\-\-list\fR).
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-date " " \fIDD/MM\fR
Filter piped (plain) output to a specific date.
.TP
.B \-\-list
List available cinema IDs and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-clear
Clear the cache for the selected cinema before fetching.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cache
Ignore the cache and always fetch fresh data.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH KEYS
.TP
.B arrow keys
Move around the poster grid.
.TP
.B enter
Open the movie's detail view (poster, plot, every day's showtimes).
.TP
.B t
Open the trailer in the browser.
.TP
.B b
Open the booking page in the browser.
.TP
.B p
Toggle the ticket price table.
.TP
.B c
Switch cinema (saved as the new default).
.TP
.B r
Refresh, ignoring the cache.
.TP
.B q / esc
Quit / go back.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/cine/config.json
Remembered default cinema.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/cine/
Cached showtimes (12 h TTL) and posters.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sips (1),
.BR open (1)
